Even As Trump Denounces Vote By Mail, GOP In Florida And Elsewhere Relies On ItEnlarge this image toggle caption Lynne Sladky/AP Lynne Sladky/APWith an election year pandemic, mail-in ballots may become an increasingly popular way to vote, especially in states like Florida that allow any voter to use them.
Mail-in ballots have also been a key tool in other Republican-friendly states such as Arizona and Utah.
In many races, both local and statewide, mail-in ballots have provided Republican candidates with the votes to win.
In recent elections, Democratic campaigns in Florida have also begun relying on mail ballots.
In Florida and elsewhere, mail ballots have been involved in election fraud, but Smith and other experts say it's rare.